comment: all these comments about amber abusing johnny....i watched an interview with johnny either yesterday or the day before where he said THEY WERE BOTH PHYSICAL WITH EACH OTHER. he also said they had to break up before things "got more fucked up". i dunno what he meant by that,but when a married couple are physically abusive WITH EACH OTHER,things are already fucked up. here amber had just been told her beloved car had been stolen for the 3RD time, and the cops were filming her because they were star struck...really,who wouldnt be pissed off in that situation? anyone who's had their car stolen or even broken into,more than knows the anger,along with sadness and other emotions you feel,when that happens to your pride and joy.amber and johhny were close here,and at the end they were both laughing and touching each other.people are "seeing" signs of her "abusive behaviour" that simply arent there.if you are going to hate on one person in a 2 person abusive marriage,it's only fair you hate on both.remember,johnny has been an actor for decades-he'd be a perfect liar and manipulator and able to hide truths.he wore ear pieces for the last  Pirates of the carribean because he was such a bad drunk and so fucked up he couldnt remember or learn  his lines-that's NOT a stable person.as for amber allegedly shitting on the bed-she allegedly told their estate manager she did it,which doesnt make sense.there's also fotos of amber with bruises and other marks from johnny, and video footage of him kicking& hitting kitchen cupboards on one particular morning drunk&pours himself another large glass of alcohol.there's a recording of him trying to get into a bathroom amber has locked herself in to get away from him.johnny is no angel,and is far from being the one and only victim.amber got $7million after her and johnny's breakup-she gave the whole lot to charity. that in itself puts the "gold digger" claims to bed.it's also not unknown for someone to have an abusive relationship with one person,and to have previous or future partners experience none of the abuse.

The majority of news articles online tacitly accept Johnny Depp as an abusive drunk.
